{"title":"Project Charter","markdown":{"headingText":"Project Charter","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Project Title\nSubsea Benthic Analysis AI – Multi-Modal Environmental Intelligence Pipeline\n\n## Sponsor\nNOAA / SUB / Petrobras\n\n## Purpose\nDevelop an Artificial Intelligence pipeline for automated identification and\nfiltering of benthic-relevant subsea data to support environmental baseline\nstudies under SUB responsibility.\n\n## Business Need\nSubsea environmental datasets require extensive manual review. Automation is\nrequired to reduce workload, increase consistency, and accelerate environmental\nassessments.\n\n## Objectives\n\n### Primary Objective (MVP)\nDevelop a binary classification system to distinguish benthic-relevant from\nnon-benthic data.\n\n### Secondary Objectives\n- Scalable multi-modal pipeline\n- AI-assisted annotation\n- Foundation for future detection, segmentation, and taxonomy\n\n## High-Level Scope\n\n### In Scope\n- Still image classification (MVP)\n- Batch, offline processing\n- AI-assisted annotation\n- Human-in-the-loop validation\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Real-time deployment\n- Full taxonomic classification\n- Advanced multimodal fusion\n\n## High-Level Success Criteria\n- Precision ≥ 75% (benthic class)\n- Dataset reduction ≥ 40–60%\n- Retention ≥ 85–90% of true benthic data\n\n## High-Level Risks\n- No labeled dataset\n- Annotation subjectivity\n- Class imbalance\n- Model underperformance\n\n## Governance\nSponsor: NOAA / SUB  \nProject Manager: Assigned by SUB  \nTechnical Authority: Data Science Lead  \nScientific Authority: Marine/Environmental Lead\n\n## Approval\nThis Charter authorizes the project to proceed to Planning.\n\n\n<!--\n<br>\n\n**Sponsor Signature:** ____________________\n-->\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":